сский (Russian)\",\"language_code\":\"ru\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/ru/library/noi/preface/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Slovenčina (Slovak)\",\"language_code\":\"sk\",\"enabled\":false,\"url_path\":\"/sk/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Slovenščina (Slovenian)\",\"language_code\":\"sl\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/sl/library/noi/preface/\"},{\"display_name\":\"українська мова (Ukrainian)\",\"language_code\":\"uk\",\"enabled\":false,\"url_path\":\"/uk/\"},{\"display_name\":\"isiZulu (Zulu)\",\"language_code\":\"zu\",\"enabled\":false,\"url_path\":\"/zu/\"}],\"breadcrumb\":[{\"url_path\":\"/en/library/\",\"title\":\"Library\"},{\"url_path\":\"/en/library/noi/\",\"title\":\"Nectar of Instruction\"}],\"url_path\":\"/en/library/noi/preface/\",\"bb\":4306,\"has_advanced_view\":false,\"pager\":{\"previous\":{\"url_path\":\"/en/library/noi/\",\"title\":\"Nectar of Instruction\",\"has_advanced_view\":true,\"translations\":[\"en\",\"cs\",\"es\",\"bg\",\"pt-br\",\"ru\",\"de\",\"et\",\"ko\",\"sl\"]},\"next\":{\"url_path\":\"/en/library/noi/1/\",\"title\":\"Text One\",\"has_advanced_view\":false,\"translations\":[\"en\",\"cs\",\"es\",\"bg\",\"pt-br\",\"ru\",\"de\",\"et\",\"ko\",\"sl\"]}},\"child_items\":[{\"section\":\"before-verses\",\"section_title\":\"Before Verses\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":147378,\"bb\":5767,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/noi/preface/b5767/\",\"body_value\":\"The Kṛṣṇa consciousness movement is conducted under the supervision of Śrīla Rūpa Gosvāmī. The Gauḍīya Vaiṣṇavas, or Bengali Vaiṣṇavas, are mostly followers of Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu, of whom the Six Gosvāmīs of Vṛndāvana are direct disciples. Therefore Śrīla Narottama dāsa Ṭhākura has sung:\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"verse_text\",\"id\":147379,\"bb\":5768,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/noi/preface/b5768/\",\"body_value\":\"\u003cem\u003erūpa-raghunātha-pade ha-ibe ākuti\u003cbr /\u003ekabe hāma bujhaba se yugala-pīriti\u003c/em\u003e\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":147380,\"bb\":5769,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/noi/preface/b5769/\",\"body_value\":\"“When I am eager to understand the literature given by the Gosvāmīs, then I shall be able to understand the transcendental loving affairs of Rādhā and Kṛṣṇa.” Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu appeared in order to bestow upon human society the benediction of the science of Kṛṣṇa. The most exalted of all the activities of Lord Kṛṣṇa are His pastimes of conjugal love with the \u003cem\u003egopīs.\u003c/em\u003e Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu appeared in the mood of Śrīmatī Rādhārāṇī, the best of the \u003cem\u003egopīs\u003c/em\u003e. Therefore, to understand the mission of Lord Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu and follow in His footsteps, one must very seriously follow in the footsteps of the Six Gosvāmīs – Śrī Rūpa, Sanātana, Bhaṭṭa Raghunātha, Śrī Jīva, Gopāla Bhaṭṭa and Dāsa Raghunātha.\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":147381,\"bb\":5770,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/noi/preface/b5770/\",\"body_value\":\"Śrī Rūpa Gosvāmī was the leader of all the Gosvāmīs, and to guide our activities he gave us this \u003cem\u003eUpadeśāmṛta\u003c/em\u003e (\u003cem\u003eThe Nectar of Instruction\u003c/em\u003e) to follow. As Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu left behind Him the eight verses known as \u003cem\u003eŚikṣāṣṭaka,\u003c/em\u003e Rūpa Gosvāmī gave us \u003cem\u003eUpadeśāmṛta\u003c/em\u003e so that we may become pure Vaiṣṇavas.\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":147382,\"bb\":5771,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/noi/preface/b5771/\",\"body_value\":\"In all spiritual affairs, one’s first duty is to control his mind and senses. Unless one controls his mind and senses, one cannot make any advancement in spiritual life. Everyone within this material world is engrossed in the modes of passion and ignorance. One must promote himself to the platform of goodness, \u003cem\u003esattva-guṇa,\u003c/em\u003e by following the instructions of Rūpa Gosvāmī, and then everything concerning how to make further progress will be revealed.\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":147383,\"bb\":5772,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/noi/preface/b5772/\",\"body_value\":\"$2d\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":147384,\"bb\":5773,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/noi/preface/b5773/\",\"body_value\":\"A. C. Bhaktivedanta Swami\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":147385,\"bb\":5774,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/noi/preface/b5774/\",\"body_value\":\"September 20, 1975, Viśvarūpa-mahotsava\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":147386,\"bb\":5775,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/noi/preface/b5775/\",\"body_value\":\"Kṛṣṇa-Balarāma Mandira\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":147387,\"bb\":5776,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/noi/preface/b5776/\",\"body_value\":\"Ramaṇa-reti, Vṛndāvana, India\"}]}]}]},{\"section\":\"verses\",\"section_title\":\"Verses\",\"children\":[{\"id\":147388,\"meta\":{\"type\":\"books.Verse\",\"slug\":\"1\",\"show_in_menus\":false,\"seo_title\":\"\",\"search_description\":\"\",\"first_published_at\":null,\"alias_of\":null,\"locale\":\"en\"},\"title\":\"Text One\",\"advanced_view_url_path\":\"/en/library/noi/advanced-view/#bb5777\",\"language_menu\":[{\"display_name\":\"አማርኛ (Ethiopian)\",\"language_code\":\"am\",\"enabled\":false,\"url_path\":\"/am/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Български (Bulgarian)\",\"language_code\":\"bg\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/bg/library/noi/1/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Čeština (Czech)\",\"language_code\":\"cs\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/cs/library/noi/1/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Dansk (Danish)\",\"language_code\":\"da\",\"enabled\":false,\"url_path\":\"/da/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Deutsch (German)\",\"language_code\":\"de\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/de/library/noi/1/\"},{\"display_name\":\"English\",\"language_code\":\"en\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/