92/\",\"shadow_value\":\"\u003cem\u003etat\u003c/em\u003e – of Lord Kṛṣṇa; \u003cem\u003enāma\u003c/em\u003e – the holy name; \u003cem\u003erūpa\u003c/em\u003e – form; \u003cem\u003ecarita-ādi\u003c/em\u003e – character, pastimes and so on; \u003cem\u003esu-kīrtana\u003c/em\u003e – in discussing or chanting nicely; \u003cem\u003eanusmṛtyoḥ\u003c/em\u003e – and in remembering; \u003cem\u003ekrameṇa\u003c/em\u003e – gradually; \u003cem\u003erasanā\u003c/em\u003e – the tongue; \u003cem\u003emanasī\u003c/em\u003e – and one’s mind; \u003cem\u003eniyojya\u003c/em\u003e – engaging; \u003cem\u003etiṣṭhan\u003c/em\u003e – residing; \u003cem\u003evraje\u003c/em\u003e – in Vraja; \u003cem\u003etat\u003c/em\u003e – to Lord Kṛṣṇa; \u003cem\u003eanurāgi\u003c/em\u003e – attached; \u003cem\u003ejana\u003c/em\u003e – persons; \u003cem\u003eanugāmī\u003c/em\u003e – following; \u003cem\u003ekālam\u003c/em\u003e – time; \u003cem\u003enayet\u003c/em\u003e – should utilize; \u003cem\u003eakhilam\u003c/em\u003e – full; \u003cem\u003eiti\u003c/em\u003e – thus; \u003cem\u003eupadeśa\u003c/em\u003e – of advice or instruction; \u003cem\u003esāram\u003c/em\u003e – the essence.\",\"word_for_word_value\":[{\"word\":\"tat\",\"translation\":\"of Lord Kṛṣṇa\"},{\"word\":\"nāma\",\"translation\":\"the holy name\"},{\"word\":\"rūpa\",\"translation\":\"form\"},{\"word\":\"carita-ādi\",\"translation\":\"character, pastimes and so on\"},{\"word\":\"su-kīrtana\",\"translation\":\"in discussing or chanting nicely\"},{\"word\":\"anusmṛtyoḥ\",\"translation\":\"and in remembering\"},{\"word\":\"krameṇa\",\"translation\":\"gradually\"},{\"word\":\"rasanā\",\"translation\":\"the tongue\"},{\"word\":\"manasī\",\"translation\":\"and one’s mind\"},{\"word\":\"niyojya\",\"translation\":\"engaging\"},{\"word\":\"tiṣṭhan\",\"translation\":\"residing\"},{\"word\":\"vraje\",\"translation\":\"in Vraja\"},{\"word\":\"tat\",\"translation\":\"to Lord Kṛṣṇa\"},{\"word\":\"anurāgi\",\"translation\":\"attached\"},{\"word\":