y/bg/8/6/\\\"\u003e\u003cem\u003eBhagavad-gītā\u003c/em\u003e (8.6)\u003c/a\u003e it is said:\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"verse_text\",\"id\":147614,\"bb\":5995,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/noi/8/b5995/\",\"body_value\":\"\u003cem\u003eyaṁ yaṁ vāpi smaran bhāvaṁ\u003cbr /\u003etyajaty ante kalevaram\u003cbr /\u003etaṁ taṁ evaiti kaunteya\u003cbr /\u003esadā tad-bhāva-bhāvitaḥ\u003c/em\u003e\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":147615,\"bb\":5996,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/noi/8/b5996/\",\"body_value\":\"“Whatever state of being one remembers when he quits his body, that state he will attain without fail.”\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":147616,\"bb\":5997,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/noi/8/b5997/\",\"body_value\":\"$51\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"verse_text\",\"id\":147617,\"bb\":5998,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/noi/8/b5998/\",\"body_value\":\"\u003cem\u003ekṛṣṇaṁ smaran janaṁ cāsya\u003cbr /\u003epreṣṭhaṁ nija-samīhitam\u003cbr /\u003etat-tat-kathā-rataś cāsau\u003cbr /\u003ekuryād vāsaṁ vraje sadā\u003c/em\u003e\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":147618,\"bb\":5999,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/noi/8/b5999/\",\"body_value\":\"“A devotee should always reside in the transcendental realm of Vraja and always engage in \u003cem\u003ekṛṣṇaṁ smaran janaṁ cāsya preṣṭham,\u003c/em\u003e the remembrance of Śrī Kṛṣṇa and His beloved associates. By following in the footsteps of such associates and by entering under their eternal guidance, one can acquire an intense desire to serve the Supreme Personality of Godhead.”\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":147619,\"bb\":6000,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/noi/8/b6000/\",\"body_value\":\"Again Śrīla Rūpa Gosvāmī states in \u003cem\u003eBhakti-rasāmṛta-sindhu\u003c/em\u003e (1.2.295):\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"verse_text\",\"id\":147620,\"bb\":6001,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/noi/8/b6001/\",\"body_value\":\"\u003cem\u003esevā sādhaka-rūpeṇa\u003cbr /\u003esiddha-rūpeṇa cātra hi\u003cbr /\u003etad-bhāva-lipsunā kāryā\u003cbr /\u003evraja-lokānusārataḥ\u003c/em\u003e\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":147621,\"bb\":6002,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/noi/8/b6002/\",\"body_value\":\"“In the transcendental realm of Vraja [Vraja-dhāma] one should serve the Supreme Lord, Śrī Kṛṣṇa, with a feeling similar to that of His associates, and one should place himself under the direct guidance of a particular associate of Kṛṣṇa and should follow in his footsteps. This method is applicable both in the stage of \u003cem\u003esādhana\u003c/em\u003e [spiritual practices executed while in the stage of bondage] and in the stage of \u003cem\u003esādhya\u003c/em\u003e [God realization], when one is a \u003cem\u003esiddha-puruṣa,\u003c/em\u003e or a spiritually perfect soul.”\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":147622,\"bb\":6003,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/noi/8/b6003/\",\"body_value\":\"Śrīla Bhaktisiddhānta Sarasvatī Ṭhākura has commented as follows upon this verse: “One who has not yet developed interest in Kṛṣṇa consciousness should give up all material motives and train his mind by following the progressive regulative principles, namely chanting and remembering Kṛṣṇa and His name, form, quality, pastimes and so forth. In this way, after developing a taste for such things, one should try to live in Vṛndāvana and pass his time constantly remembering Kṛṣṇa’s name, fame, pastimes and qualities under the direction and protection of an expert devotee. This is the sum and substance of all instruction regarding the cultivation of devotional service.\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":147623,\"bb\":6004,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/noi/8/b6004/\",\"body_value\":\"$52\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":147624,\"bb\":6005,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/noi/8/b6005/\",\"body_va