sed us how to treat various devotees. We can see from practical experience that there are different types of Vaiṣṇavas. The \u003cem\u003eprākṛta-sahajiyās\u003c/em\u003e generally chant the Hare Kṛṣṇa \u003cem\u003emahā-mantra,\u003c/em\u003e yet they are attached to women, money and intoxication. Although such persons may chant the holy name of the Lord, they are not yet properly purified. Such people should be respected within one’s mind, but their association should be avoided. Those who are innocent but simply carried away by bad association should be shown favor if they are eager to receive proper instructions from pure devotees, but those neophyte devotees who are actually initiated by the bona fide spiritual master and are seriously engaged in carrying out the orders of the spiritual master should be offered respectful obeisances.\"}}]}],[\"$\",\"$L61\",\"child-147543\",{\"child\":\"$2b:props:children:0:props:children:props:page:child_items:1:children:4:child_items:4:children:8\",\"hasId\":true,\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"em:mb-4 em:leading-8 em:text-base s-justify\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"$b0\"}}]}],[\"$\",\"$L61\",\"child-147544\",{\"child\":\"$2b:props:children:0:props:children:props:page:child_items:1:children:4:child_items:4:children:9\",\"hasId\":true,\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"em:mb-4 em:leading-8 em:text-base s-justify\",\"children\":[\"The process by which a devotee becomes attached to Kṛṣṇa is described in \",[\"$\",\"$L29\",\"1\",{\"href\":\"/en/library/cc/antya/4/192/\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"em\",\"0\",{\"children\":\"Caitanya-caritāmṛta\"}],\" (\",[\"$\",\"em\",\"2\",{\"children\":\"Antya\"}],\" 4.192)\"]}],\":\"]}]}],[\"$\",\"$L61\",\"child-147545\",{\"child\":\"$2b:props:children:0:props:children:props:page:child_items:1:children:4:child_items:4:children:10\",\"hasId\":true,\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"em:mb-4 em:leading-8 em:text-base text-center italic\",\"