 in Kṛṣṇa, is the beginning of Kṛṣṇa consciousness. Faith means strong faith. The words of \",[\"$\",\"em\",\"5\",{\"children\":\"Bhagavad-gītā\"}],\" are authoritative instructions for faithful men, and whatever Kṛṣṇa says in \",[\"$\",\"em\",\"7\",{\"children\":\"Bhagavad-gītā\"}],\" is to be accepted as it is, without interpretation. This was the way Arjuna accepted \",[\"$\",\"em\",\"9\",{\"children\":\"Bhagavad-gītā\"}],\". After hearing \",[\"$\",\"em\",\"11\",{\"children\":\"Bhagavad-gītā\"}],\", Arjuna told Kṛṣṇa: \",[\"$\",\"em\",\"13\",{\"children\":\"sarvam etad ṛtaṁ manye yan māṁ vadasi keśava\"}],\". “O Kṛṣṇa, I totally accept as truth all that You have told me.” (\",[\"$\",\"$L29\",\"15\",{\"href\":\"/en/library/bg/10/14/\",\"children\":\"Bg. 10.14\"}],\")\"]}]}],[\"$\",\"$L61\",\"child-147567\",{\"child\":\"$2b:props:children:0:props:children:props:page:child_items:1:children:4:child_items:4:children:32\",\"hasId\":true,\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"em:mb-4 em:leading-8 em:text-base s-justify\",\"children\":[\"This is the correct way of understanding \",[\"$\",\"em\",\"1\",{\"children\":\"Bhagavad-gītā\"}],\", and this is called \",[\"$\",\"em\",\"3\",{\"children\":\"śraddhā\"}],\". It is not that one accepts a portion of \",[\"$\",\"em\",\"5\",{\"children\":\"Bhagavad-gītā\"}],\" according to his own whimsical interpretations and then rejects another portion. This is not \",[\"$\",\"em\",\"7\",{\"children\":\"śraddhā\"}],\". \",[\"$\",\"em\",\"9\",{\"children\":\"Śraddhā\"}],\" means accepting the instructions of \",[\"$\",\"em\",\"11\",{\"children\":\"Bhagavad-gītā\"}],\" in their totality, especially the last instruction: \",[\"$\",\"em\",\"13\",{\"children\":\"sarva-dharmān parityajya mām ekaṁ śaraṇaṁ vraja\"}],\". “Abandon all varieties of religion and just surrender unto Me.” (\",[\"$\",\"$L29\",\"15\",{\"href\":\"/en/library/bg/18/66/\",\"children\":\"Bg. 18.66\"}],\") When one becomes completely faithful in regard to this i