g another mistake. This is the way of the struggle for existence in the material world. If one in this condition is advised to take to Kṛṣṇa consciousness and be happy, he does not accept such instructions.b8:T597,S"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"uch people never surrender to Kṛṣṇa, and they oppose the endeavor of those who wish to take Kṛṣṇa’s shelter. When such atheists become leaders of society, the entire atmosphere is surcharged with nescience. In such a condition, people do not become very enthusiastic to receive this Kṛṣṇa consciousness movement, just as a diseased person suffering from jaundice does not relish the taste of sugar candy. However, one must know that for jaundice, sugar candy is the only specific medicine. Similarly, in the present confused state of humanity, Kṛṣṇa consciousness, the chanting of the holy name of the Lord – Hare Kṛṣṇa, Hare Kṛṣṇa, Kṛṣṇa Kṛṣṇa, Hare Hare/ Hare Rāma, Hare Rāma, Rāma Rāma, Hare Hare – is the only remedy for setting the world aright. Although Kṛṣṇa consciousness may not be very palatable for a diseased person, Śrīla Rūpa Gosvāmī nonetheless advises that if one wants to be cured of the material disease, he must take to it with great care and attention. One begins his treatment by chanting the Hare Kṛṣṇa \u003cem\u003emahā-mantra\u003c/em\u003e because by chanting this holy name of the Lord a person in the material condition will be relieved from all misconceptions (\u003cem\u003eceto-darpaṇa-mārjanam\u003c/em\u003e). \u003cem\u003eAvidyā,\u003c/em\u003e a misconception about one’s spiritual identity, provides the foundation for \u003cem\u003eahaṅkāra,\u003c/em\u003e or false ego within the heart."])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"84:[\"$\",\"div\",\"147589-purport,147589-purport\",{\"className\":\"av-purport\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h3\",null,{\"className\":\"text-center em:leading-5 em:text-xl font-bold em:mb-4\",\"children\":\"Purport\"}],[[\"$\",\"$L61\",\"child-147594\",{\"child\":\"$2b:props:ch